-- Pound Advances Against Dollar, Euro After U.K. House Prices Rise
-- B y   G a r t h   T h e u n i s s e n
-- 2011-02-04T08:12:10Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-04/pound-appreciates-against-dollar-and-euro-after-british-house-prices-rise.html
The pound strengthened against the
dollar and euro, extending this week’s rally, after a report
showed U.K. house prices rose in January.  Britain’s currency climbed 0.1 percent to $1.6154,
extending its advance this week to 1.8 percent. Against the
euro, the pound appreciated 0.2 percent to 84.34 pence for 1.8
percent gain for the past five days.  House prices in the U.K. rose 0.8 percent in January from
the previous month,  Lloyds Banking Group Plc ’s mortgage-lending
division Halifax said today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Garth Theunissen at 
 gtheunissen@bloomberg.net  